annotation.TEXT: To be continued... Ze!
Well, that didn't quite work... Let's try this again...
I'll just proceed along the same path that I took the first time, until I get to the broom.
Uh, oh... Okay, don't panic. This jump is still makeable.
With all these spikes around, I've gotta be careful with my movements here.
Yeah, I'll just finish now. I'm short 29 stars, but I have no idea whether any of them were in the first half of the level, or if they were all in the second half.
BTW, bootleg Yoshi isn't actually required for anything here, but she is convenient. Now, I am at 99 stars. The star I'm currently missing is... that one star...
Yeah, I'm not dealing with those unfair yellow guys. Now, as for that last star, the one that drove me nuts for several of my attempts, guess where it is!
Anyway, next time, I'll be checking out 3-2-2!
Okay, perhaps I can use the blue guy to help me get that star.
Duck jumping to hit that B switch seems to be the best bet. I've had a few failures there.
Okay, there we go! Ooh, a broom!
Alright, so up next is world 3-2-1, blastoff!
Anyway, I completed the level without dying, so that's a plus. But, who knows how tricky those remaining stars will be...
Thank you, yellow guy! Okay, I wonder if I'll need this blue guy for something, since I didn't rush as fast as I was probably supposed to during that last B switch...
I think I should be okay as long as I'm not reckless.
There's another miko suit, which I don't need right now.
On top of that, there's another miko suit at the beginning of the volcano section.
Oh, geez. That's a lot of platforms.
Hello, and welcome back to Super Marisa World! I decided to switch the files around here so that file I'm playing on is the first one.
But, a well-aimed hammer orb worked just fine!
Harding!
Oh, man. This must be the volcano part of Hills / Volcano World.
Okay, wake up, Mr. Blue Guy, so that I can try bouncing off of your head again.
Oh, well. At least I did eventually decide to check near the goal again to refind it, and now I've got my perfect.
Maybe so... Oh, man... That one star there... I guess I was supposed to race like mad during the previous B switch...
Oh, man. A load of single-block jumps...
Whoa, geez! That could've been disastrous!
Oh, and guess what? The first half of the level only contains 40 stars, so I did indeed get all of the first half's stars the first time around!
Anything to the right up here? ...Umm... I don't know.
And just like that, there's the goal! Well, I obviously just skipped a good chunk of the level, but I have no idea how easy backtracking will be, so...
Huh, now that I think about it, I do find it odd that there were no B switches in world 2, unless there's any that I forgot about... (If there were any in world 2, let me know.)
Whoa, there's duders and platforms!
Wilson!
Wow, those randomly tossed hammer orbs there totally ambushed that yellow guy on the right.
As for this star, I've never been fast enough to reach it while the B switch was still active, but bouncing off of a blue guy works just fine.
Huh. I'm surprised that duck jump worked there. But, what did I skip past by doing that?
Okay, now there is a runway down below, and a P block with meat in it up above. You can reach the meat by either bouncing off of a blue duder here, or flying from below.
LOL, these green blocks resolidified on top of this yellow guy!
Hi, Rumia!
Okay, that worked, but am I supposed to rush like crazy here? Oh, man...
If I hadn't forgotten about that one star right next to the goal that I did grab the first time, I'm sure my number of failed attempts would've been a single-digit number!
Woo, made it up just in time there. Of course, I could've found a duder to jump off of if I didn't make it.
There are some Thwomps here. Jump over the first three after they've crashed down, but don't try that with the fourth.
Okay, I'm at the broom's location.
Ugh, I can't believe what was responsible for a lot of my failures, and so much wasted time...
Yep! Okay, this'll probably get me killed, but I'm going to keep hovering to the left as far as I can, in the hopes that I'll find some stars that would otherwise be unreachable.
Oops, how'd I manage to miss the meat there? BTW, if you try bouncing off of a blue guy to reach it, I'd recommend doing so from the left, due to the spikes on the right.
And suddenly, it's laggy again.
Such scary-looking jumps...
I probably shouldn't shoot that other guy yet.
Yay, a 2x2 room dedicated just to having a checkpoint.
Gotcha! Yeah, those green guys are pests.
I did see stars further along the path below, but there is this obvious runway here...
I did have some dumb deaths, but it was basically the star searching that was time-consuming...
Okay, where are those 2 stars that I know are around here?
Clunk!
I'll be sure to point out that star when I get to it.
Hmm... I can totally just fly over that spiky pipe, right?
For the fifth one, which is guarding these ten stars, just smack it with the white FOE.
And then I go and shoot him anyway. What was I thinking? Well, no worries, since there's a Lay's Wavy blue guy right here that I can use.
Looks like I've gotta drill here, and that it'll be a one-way trip. Who knows if I've gotten every star so far, but I don't want to waste too much time looking around right now.
Yeah, it looks like I'll need to hit a B switch to continue on that way.
Oh, come on! How'd I blow it there? I knew I should've hammered that guy ahead of time, but I was kind of rushing at this point. Still, the run isn't failed yet...
LOL, of course, it would help if I hit the right button... (I accidentally hit the cancel button there.)
Hey there, hammered Thwomp. How's it going?
In fact, you might not even have to guess, because you saw me grab it just before I finished the level the first time!
Wow, I aimed that perfectly!
Uh, oh. This looks tricky.
DOUBLE KILL!
Nice. Now, I do see those P blocks up there...
I had completely forgotten about this 1 blasted star while replaying this level, and after locating the other 99 without too much trouble, I was going nuts trying to find this one!
Well, I found the B switch. Now I've gotta not slip and fall as I climb back up to it.
Yes! Also, I saw green blocks to the right that I can perhaps reach by jumping from the cloud up here...
Ugh, that green guy is in just the right spot for me to not be able to hit him with my fireball orbs...
Pfft. Really, I managed to screw up there? Well, as I just said, the run isn't failed yet, and besides, I already took out the Thwomp and green guy here.
Cool, a miko suit. Now I can start hammering everything.
Okay, now we begin for realsies.
There they were, further to the left of where I had landed after my meaty flight back there. Bye, Rumia!
Also, that first B switch is totally unnecessary. Jump from the highest platforms there, and you'll land around here. Watch out for FOEs and the gap in the ledges, though.
I've bumped into spikes in this section several times so far, but as long as I don't die, the run isn't failed yet, as the miko suit is just a convenience, and not mandatory.
Oh, man a bunch of duders, including a Chuck FOE. Also, I see a bunch of green blocks. So, it looks like we'll be encountering our first B switch since world 1!
Yes! This star right here!
LOL, what?! Okay, apparently, if you hit the meat while flying, you can still finish your current flight duration, and you'll be invisible during this! Never knew that before!
I figured out where 99 of the stars were within a fairly short amount of time, but that last remaining star... Argh, that last remaining star...
If you continue up and left from where the previous two stars I collected were, you'll find a bunch of moving platforms, and yellow guys will land on your head w/o warning.
Umm... Was I supposed to rush faster here? Well, I can still make this jump.
A couple clouds, but there's no stars or anything else of interest over here as far as I can tell.
But, this time, instead of taking off from the runway up top, I'm going to stick to the lower route, where the stars I missed the first time are.
Taft!
Huh, these stone blocks here look like they spell out "marisa".
So, it's now just a matter of getting every star in the second half of the level, including... that one star...
Anything down here? ...Just a Rex FOE, it looks like, and I needed to bounce off of him to get back up.
24 attempts later...
My accuracy with the hammer orbs has been pretty good lately!
Of course, the green guys coming up will be a greater threat now...
